•  Pemdas is order of operations. Parentheses, exponents, multiplication/division, addition/subtraction.
•  Mod is the remainder after a number is divided.  
•  Arrays hold numbers in memory. 
•  Strings allow you to enter words as a variable.
•  Infinite loops do not stop and keep repeating. 
•  Int – integers 
•  Char – a single character
•  Double – a decimal
•  String - words
•  Setw allows you to edit the output of text on the screen. The position of words on the screen can be changed. 
•  Switch statements switch the meaning of inputted variables for different cases. 
•  Boolean can only have 2 values, true or false. 
•  C++ comments are not printed on screen.